<p itemprop="description">A content designer creates and designs content that helps users complete their tasks efficiently. They understand user needs, design content strategies for digital services, and work collaboratively with multidisciplinary teams to deliver user-centred content solutions.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design content strategies based on user needs and business requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create clear, accessible content for complex digital services</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Conduct content audits and develop content improvement plans</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with user researchers to understand content performance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Work with designers and developers to implement content solutions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish and maintain content standards and style guides</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Test and iterate content based on user feedback and analytics</li>
    </ul>
</section>

